title: Question 16
prompt:
Jenna went to the video game store. She had $50 in her wallet. She sold the store 5 of her used video games for $2.00 each. She bought 2 new games on sale for $15 each.

How much money did she have left?
description: Click the <u>one best answer</u> to each question.
feedback:
This problem uses addition, subtraction, and multiplication. Jenna starts out with $50. Then, she sells 5 video games at $2 each. Multiply 5 times 2 to get $10. The $10.00 she receives is added to her original $50.00, giving her $60.00. Then, Jenna buys 2 games at $15 each. Multiply 2 times 15 to get $30. The $30.00 she spends is subtracted her $60.00, leaving her $30.00 at the end of her trip to the video game store.

Starting cash: $50.00
5 video games at $2.00 each: 5×$2.00=$10.00
2 video games at $15.00 each: 2×$15.00=$30.00
Total cash: $50.00+$10.00-$30.00=$30.00

Jenna has $30.00 left.
